  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Grace and Perseverance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "You therefore, my child, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "And the things that you have heard me say among many witnesses, entrust these to faithful men who will be qualified to teach others as well."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Join me in suffering, like a good soldier of Christ Jesus."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "A soldier refrains from entangling himself in civilian affairs, in order to please the one who enlisted him."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Likewise, a competitor does not receive the crown unless he competes according to the rules."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "The hardworking farmer should be the first to partake of the crops."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Consider what I am saying, for the Lord will give you insight into all things."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "Remember Jesus Christ, raised from the dead, descended from David, as proclaimed by my gospel,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "for which I suffer to the extent of being chained like a criminal. But the word of God cannot be chained!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "For this reason I endure all things for the sake of the elect, so that they too may obtain the salvation that is in Christ Jesus, with eternal glory."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "This is a trustworthy saying:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "If we died with Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we will also live with Him;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "if we endure,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we will also reign with Him;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "if we deny Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will also deny us;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "if we are faithless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He remains faithful,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for He cannot deny Himself.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Lord’s Approved Workman"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "Remind the believers of these things, charging them before God",
          {
            "noteId": 1128
          },
          "to avoid quarreling over words, which succeeds only in leading the listeners to ruin."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Make every effort to present yourself approved to God, an unashamed workman who accurately handles the word of truth."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "But avoid irreverent, empty chatter, which will only lead to more ungodliness,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "and the talk of such men will spread like gangrene. Among them are Hymenaeus and Philetus,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "who have deviated from the truth. They say that the resurrection has already occurred, and they undermine the faith of some."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "Nevertheless, God’s firm foundation stands, bearing this seal: “The Lord knows those who are His,”",
          {
            "noteId": 1129
          },
          "and, “Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord must turn away from iniquity.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "A large house contains not only vessels of gold and silver, but also of wood and clay. Some indeed are for honorable use, but others are for common use."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "So if anyone cleanses himself of what is unfit,",
          {
            "noteId": 1130
          },
          "he will be a vessel for honor: sanctified, useful to the Master, and prepared for every good work."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "Flee from youthful passions and pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace, together with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "But reject foolish and ignorant speculation, for you know that it breeds quarreling."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "And a servant of the Lord must not be quarrelsome, but must be kind to everyone, able to teach, and forbearing."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "He must gently reprove those who oppose him, in the hope that God may grant them repentance leading to a knowledge of the truth."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          "Then they will come to their senses and escape the snare of the devil, who has taken them captive to his will."
        ]
      }
    ],
